What problem was Docker created to solve?
Explain in terms of:
Deployment consistency
Dependency management
Infrastructure portability

Solution:-
Docker was created to solve environment inconsistency and dependency packaging problems in software delivery.

🔹 1. Dependency Hell

Applications depend on:

Specific language runtimes

OS libraries

System packages

Configuration files

On different machines:

Library versions differ

OS distributions differ

Kernel modules differ

Result → “Works on my machine” problem.

Docker solves this by packaging:

Application code

Runtime

System libraries

Dependencies
into a single immutable image.

🔹 2. Environment Drift

Traditional servers:

Long-lived

Manually configured

Hard to reproduce

Over time → configuration drift.

Docker introduced:

Immutable images

Declarative builds (Dockerfile)

Reproducible environments

Infrastructure becomes predictable.

🔹 3. Infrastructure Portability

Docker images can run anywhere:

Developer laptop

CI/CD pipeline

Cloud VM

On-prem

Kubernetes cluster

Because containers depend on:

Host kernel

Docker runtime

Not full OS virtualization.

🔹 4. Faster Delivery

Compared to VMs:

No OS boot

No hypervisor overhead

Faster startup

Easier scaling
